signatureAbility.signatureActivationDescription: Make consecutive passes for 5+ yards in air
signatureAbility.signatureDescription: Many passers use a combination mobility and aggressiveness to make big plays. When they enter the zone, they can't be intercepted (by AI defenders) while throwing on the run.
Passers with this ability are faster and more responsive to user input while scrambling behind the line of scrimmage.
While in the pocket, passers with this ability are almost guaranteed to evade the first sack attempt by a blitzing defensive back.
Passers with this ability have a higher chance of completing a pass animation (and throwing the ball) while being sacked.
Ballcarriers with this ability have faster juke animations.
Passers with this ability improve the catch rating for all running backs who are open on pass plays.
Aggressive receivers overpower defenders and attack the football. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their success rate on aggressive catches against single coverage.
Receivers with this ability run sharper routes and catch more consistently while running streak routes.
After securing a catch, ballcarriers with this ability can quickly shift momentum, change direction, and turn the corner without sacrificing speed.
Blockers with this ability reduce a pass rusher's chances of using a quick block shed move.
Blockers with this ability reduce a pass rusher's chances of using a quick block shed move.
Defenders with this ability are rarely faked out by ballcarrier moves (and cannot be faked out when user-controlled).
Defenders with this ability have faster finesse move animations during their pass rush.
Elite pass rushers are a mix of strength, speed, and tenacity. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their win rate and block shed speed against one-on-one pass blocks.
Defenders with this ability use dominant pass rush moves while rushing from the edge of the defense.
